<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Walbort:
[B]I think one thing that would help a lot is for Verant to reopen the firepot room for binding and add a cheap (20-30pp) Translocate: Timourous Deep potion so melee classes could use it. In the current game climate of distributing class abilities among other classes, giving people the ability to self-port to almost any city is not unbalancing and would be a huge improvement in gameplay experience for everyone. Wizards and druids would still be the only ones who could evac and group teleport and would still have access to teleport destinations noone else had. Getting your group together would be almost instantaneous, then you could run or port together to the destination of your choice. Yes, the world would become a little smaller, so maybe they could add a quest to be able to use the firepot room that required you to travel to each city and collect a talisman, then turn them all in to a NPC in the firepot room who would give you a single firepot key.

Just my two cents. I think that would revolutionize the game, honestly, and without unbalancing PvE in the slightest.

WW[/B][/QUOTE]

